  "texts": [
    "Another observation of outliers is the fact that the collective of authors Mangiaracina et al. (2019), analysing efficiency of last-mile delivery from a dynamic pricing aspect, is citied most frequently (115 citations in three years); however, the paper is used outside the current research topic.",
    "Another important element of bibliometric analysis is co-citation analysis.",
    "Its goal is to provide researchers with a systematic and quantitative approach to understand the structure and dynamics of the investigated research domain.",
    "The research sample covers 3296 authors, the minimum number of citation authors is 10, which identified 29 authors that meet this threshold.",
    "Figure 11 shows the co-citation network for selected authors."
  ]
}